column1: #Summary1=(human1) For spring cleaning, a vlogger goes over her old lipsticks in order to clear out expired ones, and decides to throw out her Too Faced Melted Matte Liquid, Ofra, Ashton Liquid and Urban Decay lipsticks, but not her favority red Pat McGrath lipstick, or the Dose of Color products which have no expiration date.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) During a spring cleaning session, Katie shares her experience sorting through her lipstick collection, showing how she checks expiration dates and makes decisions about which products to keep or discard based on their shelf life symbols and age.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) A YouTuber vlogs her spring cleaning of an extensive lipstick collection, discussing expiration dates, sorting expired ones for disposal, and sharing moments with her pet; She also considers storage solutions and shares her surprise about expiration symbols on cosmetics.

#Summary4=(Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct) The author is spring cleaning her makeup collection and sorting out expired lipsticks, including some that are over two years old, and discussing the shelf life of various lipsticks and why it's hard to tell if they're still good.
